WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
FORWARD OF AS A MAN THINKETH.

00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:30.380
This little volume, the result of meditation and experience, is not intended as an exhaustive

00:00:33.720 --> 00:00:48.700
It is suggestive rather than explanatory, its object being to stimulate men and women to the discovery and perception of the truth that they themselves are makers of themselves, by virtue of the thoughts which they choose and encourage.

00:00:48.700 --> 00:01:03.000
That mind is the master and weaver, both of the inner garment of character and the outer garment of circumstance, and that, as they may have hitherto woven in ignorance and pain, they may now weave in enlightenment and happiness.

00:01:28.056 --> 00:01:35.176
THOUGHT AND CHARACTER The aphorism, As a man thinketh in his heart,

00:01:35.976 --> 00:01:42.656
not only embraces the whole of man's being, but is so comprehensive as to reach out to every

00:01:42.656 --> 00:01:49.856
condition and circumstance of his life. A man is literally what he thinks, his character being the

00:01:49.856 --> 00:01:56.716
complete sum of all his thoughts. As the plant springs from, and could not be without, the seed,

00:01:57.396 --> 00:02:02.436
so every act of a man springs from the hidden seeds of his thought, and could not have appeared

00:02:02.956 --> 00:02:09.736
this applies equally to those acts called spontaneous and unpremeditated as to those

00:02:09.736 --> 00:02:16.576
which are deliberately executed. Act is the blossom of thought, and joy and suffering are

00:02:16.576 --> 00:02:24.196
its fruits. Thus does a man garner in the sweet and bitter fruitage of his own husbandry. Thought

00:02:24.196 --> 00:02:31.616
in the mind hath made us, what we are by thought we wrought and built. If a man's mind hath evil

00:02:31.616 --> 00:02:38.856
thoughts, pain comes on him as comes the wheel the ox behind. If one endure in purity of thought,

00:02:39.316 --> 00:02:47.476
joy follows him as his own shadow. Sure. Man is a growth by law, and not a creation by artifice,

00:02:47.996 --> 00:02:54.176
and cause and effect is as absolute and undeviating in the hidden realm of thought as in the world of

00:02:54.176 --> 00:03:00.976
visible and material things. A noble and godlike character is not a thing of favor or chance,

00:03:00.976 --> 00:03:07.536
but is the natural result of continued effort and right thinking, the effect of long-cherished

00:03:07.536 --> 00:03:14.316
association with godlike thoughts. An ignoble and bestial character by the same process

00:03:14.896 --> 00:03:21.896
is the result of the continued harboring of groveling thoughts. Man is made or unmade by

00:03:21.896 --> 00:03:28.076
himself. In the armory of thought he forges the weapons by which he destroys himself.

00:03:28.076 --> 00:03:34.916
He also fashions the tools with which he builds for himself heavenly mansions of joy and strength

00:03:34.916 --> 00:03:41.576
and peace. By the right choice and true application of thought, man ascends to the divine perfection.

00:03:42.276 --> 00:03:48.456
By the abuse and wrong application of thought, he descends below the level of beast. Between

00:03:48.456 --> 00:03:53.676
these two extremes are all of the grades of character, and man is their maker and master.

00:03:54.856 --> 00:03:59.736
Of all the beautiful truths pertaining to the soul which have been restored and brought to light in

00:03:59.736 --> 00:04:05.216
this age, none is more gladdening or fruitful of divine promise and confidence than this,

00:04:05.756 --> 00:04:11.156
that man is the master of thought, the molder of character, and the maker and shaper of condition,

00:04:11.456 --> 00:04:19.116
environment, and destiny. As a being of power, intelligence, and love, and the lord of his own

00:04:19.116 --> 00:04:25.176
thoughts, man holds the key to every situation, and contains within himself that transforming

00:04:25.176 --> 00:04:32.856
and regenerative agency by which he may make himself what he wills. Man is always the master,

00:04:33.316 --> 00:04:40.456
even in his weakest and most abandoned state. But in his weakness and degradation, he is the

00:04:40.456 --> 00:04:46.116
foolish master who misgoverns his household. When he begins to reflect upon his condition,

00:04:46.116 --> 00:04:52.096
and to search diligently for the law upon which his being is established, he then becomes the

00:04:52.096 --> 00:04:57.376
wise master, directing his energies with intelligence, and fashioning his thoughts to

00:04:57.376 --> 00:05:04.236
fruitful issues. Such is the conscious master, and man can only thus become by discovering

00:05:04.236 --> 00:05:10.316
within himself the laws of thought, which discovery is totally a matter of application,

00:05:10.316 --> 00:05:17.636
self-analysis, and experience. Only by much searching and mining are golden diamonds obtained,

00:05:18.396 --> 00:05:23.476
and man can find every truth connected with his being if he will dig deep into the mind of his

00:05:23.476 --> 00:05:29.616
soul. And that he is the maker of his character, the molder of his life, and the builder of his

00:05:29.616 --> 00:05:37.016
destiny, he may unerringly prove. If he will watch, control, and alter his thoughts, tracing

00:05:37.016 --> 00:05:43.916
their effects upon himself, upon others, and upon his life and circumstances, if he will link cause

00:05:43.916 --> 00:05:50.356
and effect by patient practice and investigation, utilizing his every experience, even to the most

00:05:50.356 --> 00:05:57.136
trivial, as a means of obtaining that knowledge of himself. In this direction, as in no other,

00:05:57.436 --> 00:06:03.516
is the law absolute that, he that seeketh findeth, and to him that knocketh, it shall be opened.

00:06:03.976 --> 00:06:07.216
For only by patience, practice, and ceaseless

00:06:07.596 --> 00:06:11.096
opportunity, can a man enter the door of the temple of knowledge.

00:06:44.128 --> 00:06:56.748
A man's mind may be likened to a garden, which may be intelligently cultivated or allowed to run wild, but whether cultivated or neglected, it must, and will, bring forth.

00:06:57.308 --> 00:07:05.648
If no useful seeds are put into it, then an abundance of useless seeds will fall therein, and will continue to produce their kind.

00:07:06.828 --> 00:07:26.368
Just as a gardener cultivates his plot, keeping it free from weeds and growing the flowers and fruits which he requires, so may a man tend the garden of his mind, weeding out all the wrong, useless, and impure thoughts, and cultivating toward perfection the flowers and fruits of right, useful, and pure thoughts.

00:07:27.008 --> 00:07:34.948
By pursuing this process, a man sooner or later discovers that he is the master gardener of his soul, the director of his life.

00:07:35.648 --> 00:07:47.888
He also reveals within himself the laws of thought, and understands with ever-increasing accuracy how the thought-forces and mind-elements operate in the shaping of his character, circumstances, and destiny.

00:07:48.988 --> 00:08:03.608
Thought and character are one, and as character can only manifest and discover itself through environment and circumstance, the outer conditions of a person's life will always be found to be harmoniously related to his inner state.

00:08:03.608 --> 00:08:20.968
This does not mean that a man's circumstances at any given time are an indication of his entire character, but that those circumstances are so intimately connected with some vital thought-element within himself that, for the time being, they are indispensable to his development.

00:08:21.908 --> 00:08:35.708
Every man is where he is by the law of his being. The thoughts which he has built into his character have brought him there, and in the arrangement of his life there is no element of chance, but all is the result of a law which cannot err.

00:08:36.608 --> 00:08:42.648
This is just as true of those who feel out of harmony with their surroundings as of those who are contented with them.

00:08:42.648 --> 00:08:57.708
As a progressive and evolving being, man is where he is that he may learn that he may grow, and as he learns the spiritual lesson which any circumstance contains for him, it passes away and gives place to other circumstances.

00:08:57.708 --> 00:09:16.248
Man is buffeted by circumstances so long as he believes himself to be the creature of outside conditions, but when he realizes that he is a creative power and that he may command the hidden soil and seeds of his being out of which his circumstances grow, he then becomes the rightful master of himself.

00:09:17.108 --> 00:09:32.508
That circumstances grow out of thought, every man knows who has for any length of time practiced self-control and self-purification, for he will have noticed that the alteration in his circumstances has been an exact ratio with his altered mental condition.

00:09:33.308 --> 00:09:44.448
So true is this that when a man earnestly applies himself to remedy the defects in his character and makes swift and marked progress, he passes rapidly through a succession of vicissitudes.

00:09:45.448 --> 00:10:04.748
The soul attracts that which it secretly harbors, that which it loves, and also that which it fears. It reaches the height of its cherished aspirations, it falls to the level of its unchastened desires, and circumstances are the means by which the soul receives its own.

00:10:05.488 --> 00:10:18.488
Every thought seed sown or allowed to fall into the mind and to take root there produces its own blossoming sooner or later into act and bearing its own fruitage of opportunity and circumstance.

00:10:19.608 --> 00:10:22.708
Good thoughts bear good fruit, bad thoughts bad fruit.

00:10:23.568 --> 00:10:34.188
The outer world of circumstance shapes itself to the inner world of thought, and both pleasant and unpleasant external conditions are factors which make for the ultimate good of the individual.

00:10:34.748 --> 00:10:39.928
As the reaper of his own harvest, man learns both by suffering and bliss.

00:10:41.468 --> 00:10:50.608
A man does not come to the almshouse or the jail by the tyranny of fate of circumstance, but by the pathway of groveling thoughts and base desires.

00:10:50.608 --> 00:10:57.408
Nor does a pure-minded man fall suddenly into crime by stress of any mere external force.

00:10:58.228 --> 00:11:05.128
The criminal thought had long been secretly fostered in his heart, and the hour of opportunity revealed its gathered power.

00:11:06.768 --> 00:11:10.428
Circumstance does not make the man, it reveals him to himself.

00:11:11.228 --> 00:11:24.648
No such conditions can exist as descending into vice and its attendant sufferings apart from vicious inclinations, or ascending into virtue and its pure happiness without the continued cultivation of virtuous aspirations.

00:11:26.068 --> 00:11:33.368
And man, therefore, as the lord and master of thought, is the maker of himself, the shaper and author of environment.

00:11:34.088 --> 00:11:48.208
Even at birth the soul comes to its own, and through every step of its earthly pilgrimage it attracts those combinations of conditions which reveal itself, which are the reflections of its own purity and impurity, its strength and weakness.

00:11:50.208 --> 00:11:54.268
Men do not attract that which they want, but that which they are.

00:11:54.948 --> 00:12:04.828
Their whims, fancies, and ambitions are thwarted at every step, but their inmost thoughts and desires are fed with their own food, be it foul or clean.

00:12:05.268 --> 00:12:11.268
The divinity that shapes our ends is in ourselves, it is our very self.

00:12:12.248 --> 00:12:19.628
Man is manacled only by himself. Thought and action are the jailers of fate, they imprison, being base.

00:12:19.628 --> 00:12:24.148
They are also the angels of freedom, they liberate, being noble.

00:12:25.228 --> 00:12:29.248
Not what he wishes and prays for does man get, but what he justly earns.

00:12:29.828 --> 00:12:35.868
His wishes and prayers are only gratified and answered when they harmonize with his thoughts and actions.

00:12:37.268 --> 00:12:42.868
In the light of this truth, what, then, is the meaning of fighting against circumstances?

00:12:42.868 --> 00:12:52.688
It means that a man is continually revolting against an effect without, while all the time he is nourishing and preserving its cause in his heart.

00:12:53.528 --> 00:13:06.008
That cause may take the form of a conscious vice or an unconscious weakness, but whatever it is, it stubbornly retards the efforts of its possessor, and thus calls aloud for remedy.

00:13:07.268 --> 00:13:12.128
Men are anxious to improve their circumstances, but are unwilling to improve themselves.

00:13:12.128 --> 00:13:14.828
They, therefore, remain bound.

00:13:15.768 --> 00:13:23.148
The man who does not shrink from self-crucifixion can never fail to accomplish the object upon which his heart is set.

00:13:24.108 --> 00:13:27.268
This is as true of earthly as of heavenly things.

00:13:27.888 --> 00:13:36.108
Even the man whose sole object is to acquire wealth must be prepared to make great personal sacrifices before he can accomplish his object.

00:13:36.108 --> 00:13:41.508
And how much more so he who would realize a strong and well-poised life.

00:13:42.728 --> 00:13:44.568
Here is a man who is wretchedly poor.

00:13:45.128 --> 00:13:49.568
He is extremely anxious that his surroundings and home comforts should be improved.

00:13:50.208 --> 00:13:59.028
Yet all the time he shirks his work, and considers he is justified in trying to deceive his employer on the ground of the insufficiency of his wages.

00:13:59.848 --> 00:14:06.208
Such a man does not understand the simplest rudiments of those principles which are the basis of true prosperity.

00:14:08.168 --> 00:14:21.828
He is not only totally unfitted to rise out of his wretchedness, but is actually attracting to himself a still deeper wretchedness by dwelling in and acting out indolent, deceptive, and unmanly thoughts.

00:14:22.808 --> 00:14:29.028
Here is a rich man who is the victim of a painful and persistent disease as the result of gluttony.

00:14:29.548 --> 00:14:35.648
He is willing to give large sums of money to get rid of it, but he will not sacrifice his gluttonous desires.

00:14:36.408 --> 00:14:41.528
He wants to gratify his taste for rich and unnatural foods, and have his health as well.

00:14:42.308 --> 00:14:48.788
Such a man is totally unfit to have health, because he has not yet learned the first principles of a healthy life.

00:14:49.808 --> 00:15:02.168
Here is an employer of labor who adopts crooked measures to avoid paying the regulation wage, and, in the hope of making larger profits, reduces the wages of his work people.

00:15:03.128 --> 00:15:17.088
Such a man is altogether unfitted for prosperity. When he finds himself bankrupt, both as regards reputation and riches, he blames circumstances, not knowing that he is the sole author of his condition.

00:15:17.788 --> 00:15:27.368
I have introduced these three cases merely as illustrative of the truth that man is the causer, though nearly always unconsciously, of his circumstances.

00:15:28.168 --> 00:15:37.268
That while aiming at a good end, he is continually frustrating its accomplishment by encouraging thoughts and desires which cannot possibly harmonize with that end.

00:15:37.948 --> 00:15:43.388
Such cases could be multiplied and varied almost indefinitely, but this is not necessary.

00:15:43.868 --> 00:15:54.588
The reader can, if he so resolves, trace the actions of the laws of thought in his own mind and life, and until this is done, mere external facts cannot serve as a ground of reasoning.

00:15:55.968 --> 00:16:13.428
Circumstances, however, are so complicated, thought is so deeply rooted, and the conditions of happiness vary so vastly with individuals, that a man's entire sole condition, although it may be known to himself, cannot be judged by another from the external aspect of his life alone.

00:16:13.428 --> 00:16:22.588
A man may be honest in certain directions, yet suffer privations. A man may be dishonest in certain directions, yet acquire wealth.

00:16:23.488 --> 00:16:42.128
But the conclusion usually formed that the one man fails because of his particular honesty, and that the other prospers because of his particular dishonesty, is the result of a superficial judgment, which assumes that the dishonest man is almost totally corrupt and the honest man almost entirely virtuous.

00:16:42.128 --> 00:16:48.268
In the light of a deeper knowledge and wider experience, such judgment is found to be erroneous.

00:16:49.008 --> 00:16:58.148
The dishonest man may have some admirable virtues which the other does not possess, the honest man obnoxious vices which are absent in the other.

00:16:58.728 --> 00:17:06.628
The honest man reaps the good result of his honest thoughts and acts. He also brings upon himself the sufferings which his vices produce.

00:17:07.348 --> 00:17:11.768
The dishonest man likewise garners his own suffering and happiness.

00:17:12.728 --> 00:17:33.928
It is pleasing to human vanity to believe that one suffers because of one's virtue, but not until a man has extirpated every sickly, bitter, and impure thought from his mind, and washed every sinful stain from his soul, can he be in a position to know and declare that his sufferings are the result of his good and not of his bad qualities.

00:17:34.628 --> 00:17:46.468
And on the way to that supreme perfection, he will have found, working in his mind and life, the great law which is absolutely just, and which cannot give good for evil, evil for good.

00:17:47.368 --> 00:18:04.268
Possessed of such knowledge, he will then know, looking back upon his past ignorance and blindness, that his life is, and always was, justly ordered, and that all his past experiences, good and bad, were the equitable outworking of his evolving yet unevolved self.

00:18:05.488 --> 00:18:08.708
Good thoughts and actions can never produce bad results.

00:18:09.328 --> 00:18:12.068
Bad thoughts and actions can never produce good results.

00:18:12.708 --> 00:18:18.408
This is but saying that nothing can come from corn but corn, nothing from nettles but nettles.

00:18:18.948 --> 00:18:32.268
Men understand this law in the natural world, and work with it, but few understand it in the mental and moral world, though its operation there is just as simple and undeviating, and they therefore do not cooperate with it.

00:18:33.568 --> 00:18:37.088
Suffering is always the effect of wrong thought in some direction.

00:18:37.868 --> 00:18:43.628
It is an indication that the individual is out of harmony with himself, with the law of his being.

00:18:44.428 --> 00:18:50.528
The sole and supreme use of suffering is to purify, to burn out all that is useless and impure.

00:18:51.428 --> 00:18:53.688
Suffering ceases for him who is pure.

00:18:54.368 --> 00:19:02.048
There could be no object in burning gold after the dross has been removed, and a perfectly pure and enlightened being could not suffer.

00:19:03.168 --> 00:19:08.988
The circumstances which a man encounters with suffering are the result of his own mental in-harmony.

00:19:09.728 --> 00:19:15.448
The circumstances which a man encounters with blessedness are the result of his own mental harmony.

00:19:16.468 --> 00:19:20.708
Blessedness, not material possessions, is the measure of right thought.

00:19:21.528 --> 00:19:26.468
Wretchedness, not lack of material possessions, is the measure of wrong thought.

00:19:27.688 --> 00:19:31.528
A man may be cursed and rich, he may be blessed and poor.

00:19:32.488 --> 00:19:38.068
Blessedness and riches are only joined together when the riches are rightly and wisely used,

00:19:38.628 --> 00:19:45.028
and the poor man only descends into wretchedness when he regards his lot as a burden unjustly imposed.

00:19:46.528 --> 00:19:50.088
Indigence and indulgence are the two extremes of wretchedness.

00:19:51.088 --> 00:19:54.888
They are both equally unnatural and the result of mental disorder.

00:19:56.008 --> 00:20:00.728
A man is not rightly conditioned until he is a happy, healthy, and prosperous being.

00:20:01.528 --> 00:20:07.628
And happiness, health, and prosperity are the result of a harmonious adjustment of the inner with the outer.

00:20:08.508 --> 00:20:16.628
A man only begins to be a man when he ceases to whine and revile, and commences to search for the hidden justice which regulates his life.

00:20:17.588 --> 00:20:24.008
And as he adapts his mind to that regulating factor, he ceases to accuse others as the cause of his condition,

00:20:24.348 --> 00:20:26.948
and builds himself up in strong and noble thoughts.

00:20:26.948 --> 00:20:34.348
He ceases to kick against circumstances, but begins to use them as aids to his more rapid progress,

00:20:34.848 --> 00:20:38.748
and as a means of discovering the hidden powers and possibilities within himself.

00:20:40.208 --> 00:20:43.948
Law, not confusion, is the dominating principle in the universe.

00:20:44.448 --> 00:20:48.888
Justice, not injustice, is the soul and substance of life.

00:20:49.468 --> 00:20:55.448
And righteousness, not corruption, is the molding and moving force in the spiritual government of the world.

00:20:55.448 --> 00:21:01.548
This being so, man has but to right himself to find that the universe is right.

00:21:01.968 --> 00:21:11.988
And during the process of putting himself right, he will find that as he alters his thoughts towards things and other people, things and other people will alter toward him.

00:21:13.268 --> 00:21:21.708
The proof of this truth is in every person, and it therefore admits of easy investigation by systematic introspection and self-analysis.

00:21:21.708 --> 00:21:30.608
Let a man radically alter his thoughts, and he will be astonished at the rapid transformation it will affect in the material condition of his life.

00:21:31.848 --> 00:21:34.928
Men imagine that thought can be kept secret, but it cannot.

00:21:35.688 --> 00:21:40.668
It rapidly crystallizes into habit, and habit solidifies into circumstance.

00:21:41.688 --> 00:21:50.448
Bestial thoughts crystallize into habits of drunkenness and sensuality, which solidify into circumstances of destitution and disease.

00:21:50.448 --> 00:21:59.948
Impure thoughts of every kind crystallize into innervating and confusing habits, which solidify into distracting and adverse circumstances.

00:22:00.868 --> 00:22:13.208
Thoughts of fear, doubt and indecision crystallize into weak, unmanly and irresolute habits, which solidify into circumstances of failure, indigence and slavish dependence.

00:22:14.788 --> 00:22:23.688
Lazy thoughts crystallize into habits of uncleanliness and dishonesty, which solidify into circumstances of foulness and beggary.

00:22:24.228 --> 00:22:33.608
Hateful and condemnatory thoughts crystallize into habits of accusation and violence, which solidify into circumstances of injury and persecution.

00:22:34.808 --> 00:22:42.528
Selfish thoughts of all kinds crystallize into habits of self-seeking, which solidify into circumstances more or less distressing.

00:22:42.528 --> 00:22:53.128
On the other hand, beautiful thoughts of all kinds crystallize into habits of grace and kindliness, which solidify into genial and sunny circumstances.

00:22:54.068 --> 00:23:01.728
Pure thoughts crystallize into habits of temperance and self-control, which solidify into circumstances of repose and peace.

00:23:02.548 --> 00:23:11.928
Thoughts of courage, self-reliance and decision crystallize into manly habits, which solidify into circumstances of success, plenty and freedom.

00:23:12.868 --> 00:23:20.248
Energetic thoughts crystallize into habits of cleanliness and industry, which solidify into circumstances of pleasantness.

00:23:21.408 --> 00:23:28.908
Gentle and forgiving thoughts crystallize into habits of gentleness, which solidify into protective and preservative circumstances.

00:23:30.268 --> 00:23:40.508
Loving and unselfish thoughts crystallize into habits of self-forgetfulness for others, which solidify into circumstances of sure and abiding prosperity and true riches.

00:23:41.628 --> 00:23:49.808
A particular train of thought persisted in, be it good or bad, cannot fail to produce its results on the character and circumstances.

00:23:50.608 --> 00:23:59.208
A man cannot directly choose his circumstances, but he can choose his thoughts, and so indirectly, yet surely, shape his circumstances.

00:24:00.568 --> 00:24:04.728
Nature helps every man to the gratification of the thoughts which he most encourages,

00:24:04.728 --> 00:24:11.588
and opportunities are presented which will most speedily bring to the surface both the good and evil thoughts.

00:24:13.088 --> 00:24:18.948
Let a man cease from his sinful thoughts, and all the world will soften toward him and be ready to help him.

00:24:19.308 --> 00:24:26.228
Let him put away his weakly and sickly thoughts, and lo, opportunities will spring up on every hand to aid his strong resolves.

00:24:27.168 --> 00:24:33.068
Let him encourage good thoughts, and no hard fate shall bind him down to wretchedness and shame.

00:24:33.068 --> 00:24:44.968
The world is your kaleidoscope, and the varying combinations of colors which at every succeeding moment it presents to you are the exquisitely adjusted pictures of your ever-moving thoughts.

00:24:45.328 --> 00:24:47.908
You will be what you will to be.

00:24:48.368 --> 00:24:54.868
Let failure find its false content in that poor word environment, but spirit scorns it and is free.

00:24:54.868 --> 00:25:05.568
It masters time, it conquers space, it cows that boastful trickster chance, and bids the tyrant circumstance uncrown and fill a servant's place.

00:25:06.128 --> 00:25:15.828
The human will, that force unseen, the offspring of a deathless soul, can hew away to any goal, though walls of granite intervene.

00:25:15.828 --> 00:25:24.928
Be not impatient in delay, but wait as one who understands, when spirit rises and commands, that gods are ready to obey.

00:25:54.580 --> 00:25:57.220
EFFECT OF THOUGHT ON HEALTH AND THE BODY.

00:25:57.620 --> 00:25:59.500
The body is the servant of the mind.

00:26:00.020 --> 00:26:02.540
It obeys the operations of the mind,

00:26:02.840 --> 00:26:04.600
whether they be deliberately chosen

00:26:04.600 --> 00:26:06.500
or automatically expressed.

00:26:07.360 --> 00:26:09.060
At the bidding of unlawful thoughts,

00:26:09.220 --> 00:26:11.940
the body sinks rapidly into disease and decay.

00:26:12.700 --> 00:26:15.060
At the command of glad and beautiful thoughts,

00:26:15.420 --> 00:26:18.240
it becomes clothed with youthfulness and beauty.

00:26:19.760 --> 00:26:22.180
Disease and health, like circumstances,

00:26:22.620 --> 00:26:23.760
are rooted in thought.

00:26:24.740 --> 00:26:26.720
Sickly thoughts will express themselves

00:26:26.720 --> 00:26:28.140
through a sickly body.

00:26:29.060 --> 00:26:31.400
Thoughts of fear have been known to kill a man

00:26:31.400 --> 00:26:33.040
as speedily as a bullet,

00:26:33.540 --> 00:26:36.220
and they are continually killing thousands of people

00:26:36.220 --> 00:26:38.320
just as surely, though less rapidly.

00:26:39.320 --> 00:26:41.180
The people who live in fear of disease

00:26:41.180 --> 00:26:42.780
are the people who get it.

00:26:43.360 --> 00:26:46.040
Anxiety quickly demoralizes the whole body

00:26:46.040 --> 00:26:48.980
and lays it open to the entrance of disease,

00:26:49.620 --> 00:26:53.120
while impure thoughts, even if not physically indulged,

00:26:53.720 --> 00:26:55.540
will soon shatter the nervous system.

00:26:56.400 --> 00:26:58.580
Strong, pure, and happy thoughts

00:26:58.580 --> 00:27:00.980
build up the body in vigor and grace.

00:27:01.840 --> 00:27:04.220
The body is a delicate and plastic instrument

00:27:04.220 --> 00:27:06.300
which responds readily to the thoughts

00:27:06.300 --> 00:27:07.600
by which it is impressed,

00:27:08.180 --> 00:27:10.440
and habits of thought will produce their own effects,

00:27:10.780 --> 00:27:12.420
good or bad, upon it.

00:27:13.920 --> 00:27:16.840
Men will continue to have impure and poisoned blood

00:27:16.840 --> 00:27:19.320
so long as they propagate unclean thoughts.

00:27:20.420 --> 00:27:23.500
Out of a clean heart comes a clean life and a clean body.

00:27:23.980 --> 00:27:27.060
Out of a defiled mind proceeds a defiled life

00:27:27.060 --> 00:27:28.600
and a corrupt body.

00:27:29.200 --> 00:27:32.460
Thought is the fount of action, life, and manifestation.

00:27:33.460 --> 00:27:35.960
Make the fountain pure, and all will be pure.

00:27:37.360 --> 00:27:39.100
Change of diet will not help a man

00:27:39.100 --> 00:27:40.620
who will not change his thoughts.

00:27:41.820 --> 00:27:43.480
When a man makes his thoughts pure,

00:27:43.860 --> 00:27:45.920
he no longer desires impure food.

00:27:46.920 --> 00:27:49.560
If you would perfect your body, guard your mind.

00:27:49.560 --> 00:27:53.420
If you would renew your body, beautify your mind.

00:27:54.140 --> 00:27:58.080
Thoughts of malice, envy, disappointment, despondency,

00:27:58.540 --> 00:28:00.420
rob the body of its health and grace.

00:28:01.320 --> 00:28:03.380
A sour face does not come by chance.

00:28:03.940 --> 00:28:05.560
It is made by sour thoughts.

00:28:06.580 --> 00:28:10.340
Wrinkles that mar are drawn by folly, passion, and pride.

00:28:11.200 --> 00:28:13.800
I know a woman of 96 who has the bright,

00:28:14.020 --> 00:28:15.380
innocent face of a girl.

00:28:16.900 --> 00:28:18.740
I know a man well under middle age

00:28:18.740 --> 00:28:21.860
whose face is drawn into inharmonious contours.

00:28:22.560 --> 00:28:25.560
The one is the result of a sweet and sunny disposition.

00:28:26.260 --> 00:28:29.500
The other is the outcome of passion and discontent.

00:28:30.480 --> 00:28:33.040
As you cannot have a sweet and wholesome abode

00:28:33.040 --> 00:28:36.320
unless you admit the air and sunshine freely into your rooms,

00:28:37.520 --> 00:28:41.720
so a strong body and a bright, happy, or serene continence

00:28:41.720 --> 00:28:44.140
can only result from the free admittance

00:28:44.140 --> 00:28:47.860
into the mind of thoughts of joy and goodwill and serenity.

00:28:49.980 --> 00:28:53.540
On the faces of the age there are wrinkles made by sympathy,

00:28:53.1000 --> 00:28:55.900
others by strong and pure thoughts,

00:28:56.320 --> 00:28:57.840
others are carved by passion.

00:28:58.600 --> 00:29:00.320
Who cannot distinguish them?

00:29:00.1000 --> 00:29:02.880
With those who have lived righteously,

00:29:03.180 --> 00:29:06.280
age is calm, peaceful, and softly mellowed,

00:29:06.280 --> 00:29:07.380
like the setting sun.

00:29:08.240 --> 00:29:11.140
I have recently seen a philosopher on his deathbed.

00:29:12.220 --> 00:29:14.260
He was not old except in years.

00:29:14.800 --> 00:29:18.300
He died as sweetly and peacefully as he had lived.

00:29:19.280 --> 00:29:22.140
There is no physician like cheerful thought

00:29:22.140 --> 00:29:24.440
for dissipating the ills of the body.

00:29:25.100 --> 00:29:27.420
There is no comforter to compare with goodwill

00:29:27.420 --> 00:29:29.1000
for dispersing the shadows of grief and sorrow.

00:29:31.060 --> 00:29:33.680
To live continually in thoughts of ill-will,

00:29:34.100 --> 00:29:36.120
cynicism, suspicion, and envy,

00:29:36.660 --> 00:29:38.940
is to be confined in a self-made prison-hole.

00:29:39.600 --> 00:29:42.860
But to think well of all, to be cheerful with all,

00:29:43.500 --> 00:29:45.820
to patiently learn to find the good in all,

00:29:46.220 --> 00:29:48.620
such unselfish thoughts are the very portals

00:29:48.620 --> 00:29:52.240
of heaven, and to dwell day by day in thoughts of peace

00:29:52.240 --> 00:29:54.940
toward every creature will bring abounding peace

00:29:54.940 --> 00:29:55.980
to their possessor.

00:30:04.722 --> 00:30:06.122
4.

00:30:27.302 --> 00:30:32.242
Thought and Purpose Until thought is linked with purpose there

00:30:32.242 --> 00:30:37.802
is no intelligent accomplishment. With the majority the bark of thought is allowed to

00:30:37.802 --> 00:30:44.082
drift upon the ocean of life. Aimlessness is of ice, and such drifting must not continue

00:30:44.082 --> 00:30:50.342
for him who would steer clear of catastrophe and destruction. They who have no central

00:30:50.342 --> 00:30:56.782
purpose in their life fall in easy prey to petty worries, fears, troubles, and self-pityings,

00:30:56.782 --> 00:31:03.462
all of which are indications of weakness, which lead, just as surely as deliberately planned

00:31:03.462 --> 00:31:10.382
sins though by a different route, to failure, unhappiness, and loss, for weakness cannot

00:31:10.382 --> 00:31:17.562
persist in a power-evolving universe. A man should conceive of a legitimate purpose in his

00:31:17.562 --> 00:31:23.802
heart and set out to accomplish it. He should make this purpose the centralizing point of his

00:31:23.802 --> 00:31:30.342
thoughts. It may take the form of a spiritual ideal, or it may be a worldly object according

00:31:30.342 --> 00:31:36.662
to his nature at the time being. But whichever it is, he should steadily focus his thought forces

00:31:36.662 --> 00:31:42.542
upon the object which he has set before him. He should make his purpose his supreme duty,

00:31:42.962 --> 00:31:48.362
and should devote himself to its attainment, not allowing his thoughts to wander away into

00:31:48.362 --> 00:31:55.182
ephemeral fancies, longings, and imaginings. This is the royal road to self-control and true

00:31:55.182 --> 00:32:00.582
concentration of thought. Even if he fails again and again to accomplish his purpose,

00:32:01.242 --> 00:32:08.162
as he necessarily must until weakness is overcome, the strength of character gained will be the

00:32:08.162 --> 00:32:13.942
measure of his true success, and this will form a new starting point for future power and triumph.

00:32:14.842 --> 00:32:20.542
Those who are not prepared for the apprehension of great purpose should fix the thoughts upon

00:32:20.542 --> 00:32:27.742
the faultless performance of their duty, no matter how insignificant their task may appear. Only in

00:32:27.742 --> 00:32:33.082
this way can the thoughts be gathered and focused, and resolution and energy be developed,

00:32:33.602 --> 00:32:38.762
which being done there is nothing which may not be accomplished. The weakest soul,

00:32:38.762 --> 00:32:44.442
knowing its own weakness and believing this truth, that strength can only be developed by

00:32:44.442 --> 00:32:50.522
effort and practice, will at once begin to exert itself, and adding effort to effort,

00:32:50.862 --> 00:32:55.422
patience to patience, and strength to strength, will never cease to develop,

00:32:55.842 --> 00:33:02.762
and will at last grow divinely strong. As the physically weak man can make himself strong by

00:33:02.762 --> 00:33:08.242
careful and patient training, so the man of weak thoughts can make them strong by exercising

00:33:08.242 --> 00:33:15.422
himself in right thinking. To put away aimlessness and weakness, and to begin to think with purpose,

00:33:15.922 --> 00:33:20.962
is to enter the ranks of those strong ones who only recognize failure as one of the pathways to

00:33:20.962 --> 00:33:27.142
attainment, who make all conditions serve them, and who think strongly, attempt fearlessly,

00:33:27.822 --> 00:33:34.922
and accomplish masterfully. Having conceived of his purpose, a man should mentally mark out a

00:33:34.922 --> 00:33:41.402
pathway to his achievement, looking neither to the right nor the left. Doubts and fears should

00:33:41.402 --> 00:33:47.882
be rigorously excluded. They are disintegrating elements which break up the straight line of

00:33:47.882 --> 00:33:54.902
effort, rendering it crooked, ineffectual, useless. Thoughts of doubt and fear never

00:33:54.902 --> 00:34:02.762
accomplish anything, and never can. They always lead to failure. Purpose, energy, power to do,

00:34:02.762 --> 00:34:09.282
and all strong thoughts cease when doubt and fear creep in. The will to do springs from the

00:34:09.282 --> 00:34:15.582
knowledge that we can do. Doubt and fear are the great enemies of knowledge, and he who encourages

00:34:15.582 --> 00:34:23.122
them, who does not slay them, thwarts himself at every step. He who has conquered doubt and fear

00:34:23.122 --> 00:34:28.982
has conquered failure. His every thought is allied with power, and all difficulties are

00:34:28.982 --> 00:34:35.722
bravely met and wisely overcome. His purposes are seasonably planted, and they bloom and bring

00:34:35.722 --> 00:34:42.242
forth fruit which does not fall prematurely to the ground. Thought allied fearlessly to purpose

00:34:42.242 --> 00:34:49.902
becomes creative force. He who knows this is ready to become something higher and stronger than a mere

00:34:49.902 --> 00:34:56.542
bundle of wavering thoughts and fluctuating sensations. He who does this has become the

00:34:56.542 --> 00:34:59.862
conscious and intelligent wielder of his mental powers.

00:35:33.540 --> 00:35:39.740
All that a man achieves, and all that he fails to achieve, is the direct result of his own thoughts.

00:35:40.920 --> 00:35:49.260
In a justly ordered universe, where loss of equipoise would mean total destruction, individual responsibility must be absolute.

00:35:50.400 --> 00:35:56.720
A man's weakness and strength, purity and impurity, are his own and not another man's.

00:35:56.720 --> 00:36:05.000
They are brought about by himself, and not by another, and they can only be altered by himself, never by another.

00:36:05.840 --> 00:36:12.740
His condition is also his own, and not another man's. His suffering and his happiness are evolved from within.

00:36:13.460 --> 00:36:18.920
As he thinks, so he is. As he continues to think, so he remains.

00:36:19.780 --> 00:36:29.100
A strong man cannot help a weaker unless the weaker is willing to be helped, and even then the weak man must become strong of himself.

00:36:30.200 --> 00:36:38.380
He must, by his own efforts, develop the strength which he admires in another. None but himself can alter his condition.

00:36:39.740 --> 00:36:47.540
It has been usual for men to think and to say, Many men are slaves because one is an oppressor. Let us hate the oppressor.

00:36:48.360 --> 00:37:00.620
Now, however, there is among an increasing few a tendency to reverse this judgment, and to say, One man is an oppressor because many are slaves. Let us despise the slaves.

00:37:01.600 --> 00:37:11.220
The truth is that oppressor and slave are cooperators in ignorance, and, while seeming to afflict each other, are in reality afflicting themselves.

00:37:11.220 --> 00:37:19.440
A perfect knowledge perceives the action of law in the weakness of the oppressed and the misapplied power of the oppressor.

00:37:20.680 --> 00:37:31.160
A perfect love, seeing the suffering which both states entail, condemns neither. A perfect compassion embraces both oppressor and oppressed.

00:37:32.240 --> 00:37:41.440
He who has conquered weakness and has put away all selfish thoughts belongs neither to oppressor nor oppressed. He is free.

00:37:42.820 --> 00:37:54.020
A man can only rise, conquer, and achieve by lifting up his thoughts. He can only remain weak and object and miserable by refusing to lift up his thoughts.

00:37:54.900 --> 00:38:12.500
Before a man can achieve anything, even in worldly things, he must lift his thoughts above slavish animal indulgence. He may not, in order to succeed, give up all animality and selfishness by any means, but a portion of it must at least be sacrificed.

00:38:12.500 --> 00:38:24.860
A man whose first thought is bestial indulgence could neither think clearly nor plan methodically. He could not find and develop his Latin resources, and would fail in any undertaking.

00:38:26.600 --> 00:38:43.060
Not having commenced manfully to control his thoughts, he is not in a position to control affairs and to adopt serious responsibilities. He is not fit to act independently and stand alone, but he is limited only by the thoughts which he chooses.

00:38:44.120 --> 00:39:02.100
There can be no progress, no achievement, without sacrifice. A man's worldly success will be in the measure that he sacrifices his confused animal thoughts and fixes his mind on the development of his plans and the strengthening of his resolution and self-reliance.

00:39:02.100 --> 00:39:21.540
And the higher he lifts his thoughts, the more manly, upright, and righteous he becomes. The greater will be his success, the more blessed and enduring will be his achievements. The universe does not favor the greedy, the dishonest, the vicious, although on the mere surface it may appear sometimes to do so.

00:39:21.540 --> 00:39:39.580
It helps the honest, the magnanimous, the virtuous. All the great teachers of the ages have declared this in varying forms. And to prove and know it, a man has but to persist in making himself more and more virtuous by lifting up his thoughts.

00:39:40.420 --> 00:40:04.700
Intellectual achievements are the result of thought consecrated to the search for knowledge or for the beautiful and true in life and nature. Such achievements may be sometimes connected with vanity and ambition, but they are not the outcome of those characteristics. They are the natural outgrowth of long and arduous effort and of pure and unselfish thoughts.

00:40:05.880 --> 00:40:28.660
Spiritual achievements are the consummation of holy aspirations. He who lives constantly in the conception of noble and lofty thoughts, who dwells upon all that is pure and unselfish, will, as surely as the sun reaches its zenith and the moon its full, become wise and noble in character and rise into a position of influence and blessedness.

00:40:29.560 --> 00:40:51.060
Achievement of whatever kind is the crown effort, the diadem of thought. By the aid of self-control, resolution, purity, righteousness, and well-directed thought, a man ascends. By the aid of animality, indolence, impurity, corruption, and confusion of thought, a man descends.

00:40:51.060 --> 00:41:06.800
A man may rise to high success in the world and even to lofty altitudes in the spiritual realm, and again descend into weakness and wretchedness by allowing arrogant, selfish, and corrupt thoughts to take possession of him.

00:41:06.800 --> 00:41:17.420
Victories attained by right thought can only be maintained by watchfulness. Many give way when success is assured and rapidly fall back into failure.

00:41:18.360 --> 00:41:34.440
All achievements, whether in the business, intellectual, or spiritual world, are the result of definitely directed thought, are governed by the same law, and are of the same method. The only difference lies in the object of attainment.

00:41:34.440 --> 00:41:46.460
He who would accomplish little must sacrifice little. He who would achieve much must sacrifice much. He who would attain highly must sacrifice greatly.

00:42:16.608 --> 00:42:22.168
Visions and Ideals The dreamers are the saviors of the world.

00:42:22.748 --> 00:42:29.208
As the visible world is sustained by the invisible, so men, through all their trials and sins and

00:42:29.208 --> 00:42:34.008
sordid vocations, are nourished by the beautiful visions of their solitary dreamers.

00:42:35.428 --> 00:42:40.988
Humanity cannot forget its dreamers. It cannot let their ideals fade and die.

00:42:41.868 --> 00:42:47.688
It lives in them. It knows them in the realities which it shall one day see and know.

00:42:48.848 --> 00:42:56.068
Composer, sculptor, painter, poet, prophet, sage, these are the makers of the afterworld,

00:42:56.408 --> 00:43:01.028
the architects of heaven. The world is beautiful because they have lived.

00:43:01.588 --> 00:43:10.128
Without them, laboring humanity would perish. He who cherishes a beautiful vision, a lofty ideal

00:43:10.128 --> 00:43:16.708
in his heart, will one day realize it. Columbus cherished a vision of another world and he

00:43:16.708 --> 00:43:22.828
discovered it. Copernicus fostered the vision of multiplicity of worlds in a wider universe

00:43:22.828 --> 00:43:29.848
and he revealed it. Buddha beheld the vision of a spiritual world of stainless beauty and

00:43:29.848 --> 00:43:38.408
perfect peace and he entered into it. Cherish your visions. Cherish your ideals. Cherish the

00:43:38.408 --> 00:43:44.188
music that stirs in your heart, the beauty that forms in your mind, the loveliness that drapes

00:43:44.188 --> 00:43:50.468
your purest thoughts, for out of them will grow all delightful conditions, all heavenly environment.

00:43:51.808 --> 00:43:57.188
Of these, if you but remain true to them, your world will at last be built.

00:43:59.788 --> 00:44:07.228
To desire is to obtain. To aspire is to achieve. Shall man's basest desires

00:44:07.228 --> 00:44:13.928
receive the fullest measure of gratification and his purest aspirations starve for lack of sustenance?

00:44:15.088 --> 00:44:21.208
Such is not the law. Such a condition of things can never obtain, ask, and receive.

00:44:22.308 --> 00:44:28.688
Dream lofty dreams and as you dream so shall you become. Your vision is the promise of what you

00:44:28.688 --> 00:44:35.008
shall one day be. Your ideal is the prophecy of what you shall at last unveil. The greatest

00:44:35.008 --> 00:44:42.428
achievement was at first and for a time a dream. The oak sleeps in the acorn. The bird waits in the

00:44:42.428 --> 00:44:50.028
egg. And in the highest vision of the soul a waking angel stirs. Dreams are the seedlings of realities.

00:44:51.468 --> 00:44:56.848
Your circumstances may be uncongenial, but they shall not long remain so if you but

00:44:56.848 --> 00:45:03.988
perceive an ideal and strive to reach it. You cannot travel within and stand still without.

00:45:04.968 --> 00:45:11.288
Here is a youth hard pressed by poverty and labor, confined long hours in an unhealthy workshop,

00:45:12.648 --> 00:45:19.608
unschooled and lacking all the arts of refinement. But he dreams of better things. He thinks of

00:45:19.608 --> 00:45:28.308
intelligence, of refinement, of grace and beauty. He conceives of, mentally builds up, an ideal

00:45:28.308 --> 00:45:34.928
condition of life. The vision of a wider liberty and a larger scope takes possession of him.

00:45:35.728 --> 00:45:41.528
Unrest urges him to take action, and he utilizes all his spare time and means,

00:45:41.848 --> 00:45:46.488
small though they are, to the development of his latent powers and resources.

00:45:47.928 --> 00:45:52.608
Very soon so altered has his mind become that the workshop can no longer hold him.

00:45:53.168 --> 00:45:58.748
It has become so out of harmony with his mentality that it falls out of his life as a garment is cast

00:45:58.748 --> 00:46:05.268
aside. And, with the growth of opportunities which fit the scope of his expanding powers,

00:46:05.708 --> 00:46:12.088
he passes out of it forever. Years later we see this youth as a full grown man.

00:46:12.748 --> 00:46:17.708
We find him a master of certain forces of the mind which he wields with worldwide influence

00:46:17.708 --> 00:46:23.588
and almost unequaled power. In his hands he holds the cords of gigantic responsibilities.

00:46:24.308 --> 00:46:30.988
He speaks, and lo, lives are changed. Men and women hang upon his words and remold their characters.

00:46:31.928 --> 00:46:37.488
And, son-like, he becomes the fixed and luminous center around which innumerable

00:46:37.488 --> 00:46:44.228
destinies revolve. He has realized the vision of his youth. He has become one with his ideal.

00:46:45.568 --> 00:46:51.248
And you, too, youthful reader, will realize the vision, not the idle wish, of your heart,

00:46:51.248 --> 00:46:58.148
be it base or beautiful or a mixture of both. For you will always gravitate toward that which

00:46:58.148 --> 00:47:04.048
you secretly most love. Into your hands will be placed the exact results of your own thoughts.

00:47:04.688 --> 00:47:10.848
You will receive that which you earn, no more, no less. Whatever your present environment may be,

00:47:11.288 --> 00:47:19.068
you will fall, remain, or rise with your thoughts, your vision, your ideal. You will become as small

00:47:19.068 --> 00:47:25.368
as your controlling desire, as great as your dominant aspiration. In the beautiful words of

00:47:25.368 --> 00:47:31.288
Stanton Kirkham Davis, you may be keeping accounts, and presently you shall walk out of the door that

00:47:31.288 --> 00:47:37.008
for so long has seemed to you the barrier of your ideals, and shall find yourself before an audience,

00:47:37.648 --> 00:47:43.528
the pin still behind your ear, the ink stains on your fingers, and then and there shall pour

00:47:43.528 --> 00:47:49.668
the torrent of your inspiration. You may be driving sheep, and you shall wander to the city,

00:47:50.408 --> 00:47:56.828
bucolic and open-mouthed, shall wander under the intrepid guidance of the spirit into the studio

00:47:56.828 --> 00:48:03.708
of the master, and after a time he shall say, I have nothing more to teach you, and now you have

00:48:03.708 --> 00:48:10.348
become the master. Who did so recently dream of great things while driving sheep? You shall lay

00:48:10.348 --> 00:48:16.848
down the saw and the plane to take upon yourself the regeneration of the world. The thoughtless,

00:48:17.068 --> 00:48:22.148
the ignorant, and the indolent, seeing only the apparent effects of things and not the things

00:48:22.148 --> 00:48:30.168
themselves, talk of luck, of fortune, and chance. Seeing a man grow rich, they say, how lucky he is.

00:48:30.848 --> 00:48:36.208
Observing another become intellectual, they exclaim, how highly favored he is.

00:48:36.208 --> 00:48:41.308
In noting the saintly character and wide influence of another, they remark,

00:48:41.748 --> 00:48:48.168
how chance aids him at every turn. They do not see the trials and failures and struggles

00:48:48.168 --> 00:48:52.588
which these men have voluntarily encountered in order to gain their experience.

00:48:53.708 --> 00:48:58.768
They have no knowledge of the sacrifices they have made, of the undaunted efforts they have

00:48:58.768 --> 00:49:04.048
put forth, of the faith they have exercised, that they might overcome the apparently

00:49:04.668 --> 00:49:10.068
insurmountable and realize the vision of their heart. They do not know the darkness and the

00:49:10.068 --> 00:49:16.548
heartaches, they only see the light and joy and call it luck. Do not see the long and arduous

00:49:16.548 --> 00:49:23.008
journey but only behold the pleasant goal and call it good fortune. Do not understand the process

00:49:23.008 --> 00:49:30.908
but only perceive the result and call it chance. In all human affairs there are efforts and there

00:49:30.908 --> 00:49:38.628
are results, and the strength of the effort is the measure of the result. Chance is not. Gifts,

00:49:38.948 --> 00:49:44.268
powers, materials, intellectual and spiritual possessions are the fruits of effort.

00:49:44.808 --> 00:49:53.108
They are thoughts completed, objects accomplished, visions realized. The vision that you glorify in

00:49:53.108 --> 00:49:58.768
your mind, the ideal that you enthrone in your heart, this you will build your life by,

00:49:58.768 --> 00:50:06.288
this you will become. End of Visions and Ideals

00:50:34.320 --> 00:50:37.120
Calmness of mind is one of the beautiful jewels of wisdom.

00:50:37.120 --> 00:50:41.020
It is the result of long and patient effort and self-control.

00:50:41.800 --> 00:50:44.880
Its presence is an indication of ripened experience,

00:50:44.980 --> 00:50:49.660
and of a more than ordinary knowledge of the laws and operations of thought.

00:50:51.040 --> 00:50:56.060
A man becomes calm in the measure that he understands himself as a thought-evolved being,

00:50:56.680 --> 00:51:01.200
for such knowledge necessitates the understanding of others as the result of thought.

00:51:01.200 --> 00:51:09.900
As he develops a right understanding and sees more and more clearly the internal relations of things by the action of cause and effect,

00:51:10.500 --> 00:51:16.640
he ceases to fuss and fume and worry and grieve, and remains poised, steadfast, serene.

00:51:17.160 --> 00:51:22.480
The calm man, having learned how to govern himself, knows how to adapt himself to others,

00:51:23.140 --> 00:51:30.040
and they, in turn, reverence his spiritual strength, and feel that they can learn of him and rely upon him.

00:51:30.040 --> 00:51:36.060
The more tranquil a man becomes, the greater is his success, his influence, his power for good.

00:51:36.860 --> 00:51:43.860
Even the ordinary trader will find his business prosperity increase as he develops a greater self-control and equanimity,

00:51:44.240 --> 00:51:48.800
for people always prefer to deal with a man whose demeanor is strongly equable.

00:51:49.400 --> 00:51:52.740
The strong, calm man is always loved and revered.

00:51:52.780 --> 00:51:57.940
He is like a shade-giving tree in a thirsty land, or a sheltering rock in a storm.

00:51:57.940 --> 00:52:02.520
Who does not love a tranquil heart, a sweet-tempered, balanced life?

00:52:02.920 --> 00:52:08.440
It does not matter whether it rains or shines, or what changes come to those possessing these blessings,

00:52:08.860 --> 00:52:11.560
for they are always sweet, serene, and calm.

00:52:11.860 --> 00:52:17.000
That exquisite poise of character which we call serenity is the last lesson of culture.

00:52:17.620 --> 00:52:20.840
It is the flowering of life, the fruitage of the soul.

00:52:21.560 --> 00:52:25.080
It is precious as wisdom, more to be desired than gold.

00:52:25.860 --> 00:52:28.580
Yea, then even fine gold.

00:52:29.440 --> 00:52:33.820
How insignificant mere money-seeking looks in comparison with a serene life,

00:52:34.400 --> 00:52:40.680
a life that dwells in the ocean of truth, beneath the waves, beyond the reach of tempests, in the eternal calm.

00:52:41.480 --> 00:52:47.900
How many people we know who sour their lives, who ruin all that is sweet and beautiful by explosive tempers,

00:52:48.080 --> 00:52:51.300
who destroy their poise of character and make bad blood.

00:52:51.300 --> 00:52:58.860
It is a question whether the great majority of people do not ruin their lives and mar their happiness by lack of self-control.

00:53:00.780 --> 00:53:03.540
How few people we meet in life who are well-balanced,

00:53:03.960 --> 00:53:08.100
who have their exquisite poise which is characteristic of the finished character.

00:53:08.960 --> 00:53:15.300
Yes, humanity surges with uncontrolled passion, is tumultuous with ungoverned grief,

00:53:15.300 --> 00:53:18.220
is blown away by anxiety and doubt.

00:53:18.620 --> 00:53:23.320
Only the wise man, only he whose thoughts are controlled and purified,

00:53:23.860 --> 00:53:27.020
makes the winds and the storms of the soul obey him.

00:53:27.800 --> 00:53:33.580
Tempest-tossed souls, wherever ye may be, under whatsoever conditions ye may live,

00:53:34.020 --> 00:53:38.460
know this, in the ocean of life the isles of blessedness are smiling,

00:53:38.920 --> 00:53:41.520
and the sunny shore of your ideal awaits your coming.

00:53:41.520 --> 00:53:44.500
Keep your hand firmly upon the helm of thought,

00:53:44.880 --> 00:53:47.460
in the bark of your soul reclines the commanding master.

00:53:47.940 --> 00:53:49.940
He does but sleep, wake him.

00:53:50.200 --> 00:53:51.640
Self-control is strength.

00:53:52.480 --> 00:53:54.020
Right thought is mastery.

00:53:54.520 --> 00:53:55.940
Calmness is power.

00:53:56.460 --> 00:53:59.160
Say unto your heart, Peace be still.
